As Chief Revenue Officer for hc1.com, Jeff’s responsibilities include leading the go to market. This includes sales, marketing, demand generation, and business development. Prior to joining hc1.com, Jeff was President of CRM at SAP, responsible for leading the end-to-end CRM business for SAP globally. This included strategy, sales, operations, M&A, and P/L.
Prior to joining SAP, Jeff was the Senior Vice President for North America Enterprise Commercial Sales for Salesforce.com, leading sales for the enterprise and commercial customer segments for North America. Jeff worked at IBM for 19 years prior to Salesforce.com in which his last role was Vice President for the Software Group responsible for IBM’s software business in the Western part of the United States. He lead over 1300 sales and technical professionals that support all IBM customers in the Western U.S. Prior to this role, he was the Vice President of Sales and Services for IBM’s Master Data Management business, leading the Product Information Management, Customer Data Integration, and the Industry Models sales and services teams. Jeff holds a B.A. from Xavier University and an MBA from the University of Illinois.



