Featured Content



















Community Awards - Vote Today!

The nominees for Appreciation Awards are in! Listed members received at least one nomination from another community member during the nomination period. The next round of voting determines the final Appreciation Award recipients. Voting is scheduled to end on August 15, 2017. We will announce award recipients in September.




Cast your vote today!
















My Next Challenge – Head of SAP Community

SAP’s Brian Ellefritz recently accepted the Head of SAP Community role. In his first blog post in this new role, Brian candidly shares why he made this decision and what it means to him personally. Find out more about Brian and his vision for the future.




Read about Brian's new role
















Community Roadmap and Release Highlights

In April, Gali Kling Schneider unveiled the road map outlining our upcoming plans and priorities for feature development for SAP Community. We were looking at the roadmap in terms of two categories: content discovery and community feel. Those categories consisted of features (e.g., the development of new functionality) that supported the overarching goals. This blog post maps out where we are as of May 31.




Read the blog post
















SAP Cloud Platform – A Positive Sum Game

SAP CTO Bjoern Goerke blogs about today’s announcement at SAPPHIRENOW in Orlando SAP: general availability of the Cloud Foundry-based environment on SAP Cloud Platform. Since its incubation, openness has been a key principle guiding every decision and many of the announcements shared today build on that philosophy.




Read the blog post
















SAP Cloud Platform – The Next Level

At the beginning of the year SAP Mentor Matthias Steiner posted a teaser on Twitter stating that 2017 would be a big year for SAP Cloud Platform and he was right! In this blog post, Matthias looks at the traditional cloud model and explains SAP’s strategy for SAP Cloud Platform.




Read the blog post
















XS Advanced Programming Model with Cloud Foundry

Cloud Foundry-based environment on SAP Cloud Platform includes an SAP HANA as a Service offering, which enables the XS Advanced Programming Model now also on SAP Cloud Platform. If you don’t know the XS Advanced Programming Model, learn more in this blog post by Sven Kohlhaas.




Read the blog post






















